preambule.al:
Considering that offences against customs law are prejudicial to
            their economic, fiscal, social, cultural, public health and
            commercial interests;

Considering that cross-frontier trafficking in narcotic drugs and
            psychotropic substances, hazardous goods, endangered species and
            toxic waste constitutes a danger to public health and to society;

Convinced that action against customs offences can be made more
            effective by close co-operation between their customs
            administrations based on clear legal provisions;

Having regard to the relevant instruments of the Customs
            Co-operation Council in particular the Recommendations on mutual
            administrative assistance of 5 December 1953;

Having regard also to international conventions containing
            prohibitions, restrictions and special measures of control in
            respect of specific goods;

li.al:
the term ``customs offence" shall mean: any breach of
                customs law as defined by the legislation of each Contracting
                Party as well as any such attempted breach;

the term ``information" shall mean: any data, documents,
                reports, certified or authenticated copies thereof or other
                communications in any format, including electronic;

whether goods which are imported into the territory of the
                  requesting Contracting Party have been lawfully exported from
                  the territory of the requested Contracting Party;

goods either in transport, in transit or in storage, and
                  means of payment used or suspected of being used to commit
                  customs offences;

examine in the offices of the requested administration the
                  documents, registers and other relevant data to extract any
                  information in respect of that customs offence;

preambule.al:
Overwegende dat inbreuken op de douanewetgeving hun economische,
            fiscale, sociale en culturele belangen en hun volksgezondheids- en
            handelsbelangen schaden;

Erkennende de noodzaak van internationale samenwerking ter zake
            van aangelegenheden die verband houden met de toepassing en
            handhaving van hun douanewetgeving;

Gelet op de van belang zijnde instrumenten van de Internationale
            Douaneraad, in het bijzonder de Aanbevelingen inzake wederzijdse
            administratieve bijstand van 5 december 1953;

li.al:
goederen in vervoer, in doorvoer of in opslag, en
                  betaalmiddelen die worden gebruikt of vermoedelijk worden
                  gebruikt om inbreuken op de douanewetgeving te maken;

kopieën maken van de documenten, registers en andere
                  gegevens die met betrekking tot die inbreuk op de
                  douanewetgeving van belang zijn;
